Andile Mngxitama In 2016 on Mandela Day BLF went to the office of the Public Protector Thuli Madonsela to demand she investigates the R26 billion stolen by white monopoly capital from the people of SA. We went to her office as part of the Mandela Day service. She called the police on us. We spent 7 nights in jail and got bail. Then we had two years of going to court. We finally did community called the police on us. We spent 7 nights in jail and got bail. Then we had two years of going to court. We finally did community service work to get the NPA out of our backs. 26 BLF members were arrested for demanding that R26 billion be returned to the people. Advocate Mkhwebane did find that ABSA and others stole the money. She is being kicked out of office for this finding. The struggle continues!!! Happy Mandela Day!!! Andile Mngxitama is the President of Black First Land First (BLF) a radical black consciousness organization. When using any of Black Opinionâ€™s content, partly or in full, kindly always provide an active hyperlink to the original material.